Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest @Lemon{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into halves. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast in oven until tender and crisped, ~{25-30%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Place @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} in a #shallow dish{} or #bowl{} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. In a separate #medium bowl{}, stir together lemon zest, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Place one @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} between two pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #rolling pin{}, or a #mallet{}, or a heavy-bottomed #pan{} until ½-inch thick. Repeat with remaining chicken. Season chicken with salt and pepper, then toss each piece in sour cream mixture to coat. Dip into panko, coating all over and pressing to adhere.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook until no longer pink in center and panko is golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. TIP: Work in batches if you can't easily fit all of the chicken in the pan. If it cools, place the chicken in the oven for a minute or two to heat it up.

Stir together remaining @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{large drizzle} in a large bowl. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Add @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} and tomatoes to bowl and toss to coat.

Divide chicken and potatoes between plates and serve with salad on the side.

> Welcome to the next level of dinnertime sophistication with this zesty breaded chicken and creamy salad combo!